column4: Hi all I have flac files that I need to convert to mp3 320kbps is there a gui program that can do that at all thanks?
sound converter
Is that easy to use?
yes
extremely (and it's gui)
sudo apt-get install soundconverter
Never used winff.  Found soundconverter and I never needed anything more.
Thats all I needed to hear lol
Sorry was talking on messenger lol
sure
CBR is better than VBR am I right?
I believe so.  VBR is lower quality but is more efficient in bits vs quality
Ok cool thanks gonna try converting now lol
sure
It isn't quick I take it lol
no converter is fast
It has worked a charm got my motorhead flacs in mp3 format now your a legen
your welcome!
For future reference as you seem like you know what your doing is there a flac cue splitter gui?
I have never heard of one.  People generally don't edit cue files by hand. Just make a new cue file.
It was one flac file that was the only problem had to use medievil cue splitter in vbox windoze lol
mmm, yeah IDK  there might be one
No worries worth a shot anyway thanks
